South Sudan&#8217;s President Salva Kiir Mayardit Picture: TIKSA NEGERI / REUTERS President Jacob Zuma is today hosting his South Sudanese counterpart Salva Kiir Mayardit of the Republic of South Sudan in Pretoria. &#8220;The two Heads of State are expected to review bilateral cooperation between their two countries as well as the latest regional political and security developments on the continent &#8221; the South African presidency said in a statement. Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa on Thursday made &#8220;a courtesy call&#8221; on the Sudanese president at the Johnny Makhathini Diplomatic Guesthouse Waterkloof Pretoria. Ramaphosa is a Special Envoy of President Zuma to South Sudan. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share